eps%20quickly%2C%20he%20said.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20anticipate%20being%20nervous%20on%20a%20flight%2C%20Menon%20said%20you%20can%20bring%20a%20tactile%20activity%20with%20you%2C%20such%20as%20crocheting%2C%20drawing%2C%20or%20playing%20with%20a%20fidget%20toy.%20%26quot%3BEngaging%20multiple%20senses%20allows%20us%20to%20anchor%20our%20minds%20and%20bodies%20into%20the%20present%20moment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c6f517b0-3fa2-4bdf-a5b8-5c9a46c2e031%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETry%20the%204-7-8%20breathing%20trick%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20sounds%20simple%2C%20but%20breathing%20exercises%20work%20to%20quell%20your%20fears.%20Mindful%20breathing%20%26quot%3Bslows%20down%20our%20heart%20rate%20and%20triggers%20the%20relaxation%20response%2C%26quot%3B%20Menon%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMenon%20recommended%20the%204-7-8%20breathing%20pattern%2C%20in%20which%20you%20inhale%20for%20four%20seconds%2C%20hold%20for%20seven%2C%20and%20exhale%20for%20eight.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBunn%20agreed.%20He%20said%20exhaling%20for%20longer%20than%20you%20inhale%20is%20his%20trick%20for%20calming%20the%20nervous%20system.%20He%20added%20that%20it%20may%20not%20be%20a%20perfect%20cure-all%2C%20especially%20in%20times%20of%20turbulence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20the%20plane%20drops%2C%20everybody's%20going%20to%20get%20some%20stress%20hormones%20released%2C%20some%20more%20than%20others%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20get%20the%20most%20out%20of%20this%20trick%2C%20Menon%20said%20it's%20best%20to%20do%20it%20a%20few%20times%20prior%20to%20boarding%20the%20aircraft%2C%20as%20well%20as%20when%20you%20just%20sat%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22bad8fdc3-81bd-427d-ada5-ccd6c5968ee3%5C%22%3ELook%20at%20other%20stressors%20in%20your%20life%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20suddenly%20developed%20aerophobia%20as%20an%20adult%2C%20Bunn%20said%20it%20could%20help%20to%20look%20at%20other%20stressors%20in%20your%20life%2C%20particula