%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERemote%20living%20has%20taught%20us%20to%20be%20more%20self-sufficient%20in%20many%20ways.%3Cp%3EHilary%20Messer-Barrow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20regularly%20travel%20from%20our%20small%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-living-in-super-small-community-in-canada-2022-3%5C%22%3Eremote%20community%20in%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20the%20nearest%20city%20to%20run%20errands.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWe%20go%20to%20appointments%20and%20stock%20up%20on%20two%20months'%20worth%20of%20groceries%20when%20we%20drive%20to%20the%20city.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20best%20part%20of%20the%2010-hour%20round%20trip%20is%20an%20incredible%20drive%20home%20through%20pristine%20wilderness.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20five%20years%20ago%2C%20I%20moved%20from%20Vancouver%20to%20Beaver%20Creek%2C%20a%20community%20of%20about%2080%20residents%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-living-in-super-small-community-in-canada-2022-3%5C%22%3Eremote%20Yukon%2C%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsurprising-things-living-in-super-small-community-in-canada-2022-4%5C%22%3Emoving%20from%20a%20city%20to%20a%20remote%20area%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20northern%20Canada%2C%20I%20realized%20even%20normal%20tasks%20like%20getting%20groceries%20can%20be%20a%20huge%20undertaking.%20So%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20made%20a%20solid%20routine%20for%20running%20errands%20that%20we've%20stuck%20to%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEvery%20six%20to%20eight%20weeks%2C%20my%20husband%2C%20our%20dog%2C%20and%20I%20drive%20300%20miles%20from%20our%20remote%20northern%20community%20to%20Whitehorse%2C%20Yukon%2C%20to%20buy%20groceries%20and%20attend%20medical%20appointments.%20The%20round-trip%20drive%20is%20about%20600%20miles%20and%20takes%20about%2010%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20general%2C%20we%20try%20to%20be%20as%20efficient%20as%20possible%20when%20working%20with%20darkness%20and%20extremely%20cold%20temperatures.%20During%20seasons%20when%20we%20get%20only%20four%20hours%20of%20sunlight%20and%20extremely%20cold%20temperatures%2C%20we%20stay%20overnight%20in%20Whitehorse.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20what%20one%20of%20our%20typical%20trips%20is%20like.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EI%20got%20up%20early%20and%20began%20my%20day%20by%20warming%20up%20my%20truck%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20we%20crammed%20two%20months'%20worth%20of%20appointments%2C%20shopping%2C%20and%20errands%20into%20our%20trip%20to%20Whitehorse%2C%20we%20got%20started%20early.%20On%20this%20particular%20day%2C%20the%20sun%20didn't%20rise%20until%20noon%2C%20and%20it%20was%20-40%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20outside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20cold%20can%20be%20hard%20on%20vehicles%2C%20so%20it's%20important%20that%20we%20let%20our%20truck%20warm%20up%20for%20a%20while%20before%20heading%20out.%20Before%20driving%20to%20town%2C%20we%20also%20prepare%20by%20packing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhome-emergency-kit-products%5C%22%3Eemergency%20gear%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20trip%2C%20we%20took%20a%20satellite%20communication%20device%2C%20extra%20warm%20clothes%2C%20food%2C%20water%2C%20and%20car-repair%20equipment.%20We%20can%20never%20be%20too%20careful%20when%20traveling%20a%20long%20distance%20in%20extreme%20cold%20(and%2C%20for%20parts%20of%20the%20trip%2C%20darkness).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhile%20the%20truck%20warmed%20up%2C%20I%20walked%20our%20dog%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222316%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Selfie%20of%20the%20writer%20in%20a%20parka%20and%20scarf%20with%20snow%20covering%20her%20eyelashes%20and%20scarf%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F642f11340c909100186bfe1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221741%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMy%20face%20was%20covered%20with%20snow%20by%20the%20time%20I%20got%20in%20the%20truck.%3Cp%3EHilary%20Messer-Barrow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20taking%20our%20dog%20on%20a%20pre-drive%20walk%2C%20I%20put%20on%20more%20layers%20than%20I%20could%20count%20and%20topped%20them%20with%20a%20thick%20parka.%20I%20also%20wore%20a%20face%20covering%2C%20hat%2C%20snow%20pants%2C%20and%20winter%20boots.%20I%20bundled%20our%20dog%20up%20in%20booties%2C%20a%20thermal%20layer%2C%20and%20a%20jacket.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBecause%20of%20the%20cold%2C%20our%20morning%20walk%20wasn't%20as%20long%20as%20it%20normally%20is.%20Still%2C%20the%20truck%20was%20warmed%20and%20ready%20to%20go%20by%20the%20time%20we%20returned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20started%20driving%2C%20we%20passed%20many%20trucks%20and%20cars%20across%20town%20that%20had%20been%20left%20running%2C%20some%20without%20people%20inside.%20Not%20turning%20your%20car%20off%20while%20you%20run%20into%20a%20store%20or%20have%20lunch%20is%20normal%20here%20when%20it's%20extremely%20cold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWe%20try%20to%20run%20as%20many%20errands%20as%20possible%20when%20we're%20in%20town%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20our%20community%20has%20a%20small%20health%20center%20staffed%20with%20a%20nurse%20and%20receptionist%20and%20a%20doctor%20visits%20two%20days%20a%20month%2C%20we%20have%20to%20travel%20to%20Whitehorse%20for%20specialist%20appointments%20or%20procedures%20like%20X-rays%2C%20ultrasounds%2C%20and%20certain%20blood%20tests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20on%20this%20trip%2C%20our%20first%20stop%20of%20the%20day%20was%20the%20town's%20hospital%20so%20I%20could%20get%20routine%20blood%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20we%20headed%20to%20the%20vet's%20office%20to%20grab%20over%20100%20pounds%20of%20dog%20food%20(enough%20for%20about%20three%20months).%20We%20like%20to%20have%20extra%20on%20hand%20in%20case%20we're%20not%20able%20to%20complete%20our%20trip%20in%20good%20time.%20After%20all%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthings-you-should-not-buy-on-trips-to-save-money-frequent-traveler%5C%22%3Eplanning%20for%20contingencies%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20huge%20part%20of%20living%20in%20a%20remote%20community.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20made%20a%20quick%20stop%20at%20the%20pet-supply%20store%20for%20treats%20and%20a%20few%20new%20toys%20for%20our%20dog%2C%20too.%20We%20always%20bring%20him%20with%20us%20to%20Whitehorse%2C%20so%20we%20try%20to%20make%20sure%20he%20has%20a%20good%20time%20on%20the%20trip.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20split%20up%20to%20run%20the%20next%20few%20errands%20on%20our%20list.%20While%20he%C2%A0picked%20up%20a%20new%20saw%2C%20fuel%20for%20the%20chainsaw%2C%20and%20a%20waffle%20maker%20at%20the%20hardware%20store%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20hair%20salon.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20had%20been%20three%20months%20since%20my%20last%20visit%2C%20so%20my%20roots%20were%20in%20desperate%20need%20of%20attention.%20As%20my%20stylist%20applied%20color%2C%20she%20said%20she'd%20be%20away%20the%20next%20time%20we%20were%20in%20town.%20Unfortunately%2C%20this%20meant%20I'd%20have%20to%20go%20three%20more%20months%20without%20seeing%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20my%20hair%20appointment%2C%20I%20took%20a%20cold%2C%20quick%20walk%20to%20other%20shops%20so%20I%20could%20pick%20up%20new%20wool%20socks%2C%20a%20gift%20for%20a%20friend%2C%20and%20some%20candles.%20Meanwhile%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20our%20dog%20braved%20the%20cold%20for%20another%20short%20walk.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EGrocery%20shopping%20is%20done%20last%20because%20it%20requires%20a%20lot%20of%20effort%20and%20planning%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Full%20shopping%20cart%20with%20mostly%20produce%20and%20dairy%20products%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64347dffca216e001820fa3d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222274%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20got%20mainly%20fresh%20produce%20and%20dairy%20products.%3Cp%3EHilary%20Messer-Barrow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20we%20reconvened%20at%20the%20truck%2C%20we%20went%20to%20buy%20groceries.%C2%A0As%20usual%2C%20our%20list%20was%20long%20because%20we%20needed%20enough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-i-make-groceries-last-longer-remote-living-2023-1%5C%22%3Efood%20to%20last%20us%20nearly%20two%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20any%20special%20events%2C%20birthdays%2C%20holidays%2C%20or%20get-togethers%20we'd%20have%20during%20that%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20time%20we%20were%20done%2C%20our%20cart%20was%20so%20full%20that%20some%20more%20local%20shoppers%20asked%20us%20why%20we%20were%20purchasing%20so%20many%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%2C%20we%20began%20sorting%20ingredients%20into%20reusable%20bags%2C%20canvas%20totes%2C%20and%20coolers%20as%20the%20cashier%20scanned%20them.%20We%20packed%20frozen%20foods%20into%20the%20totes%20because%20they'd%20be%20OK%20in%20the%20-40-degree%20weather%20and%20put%20produce%20and%20dairy%20products%20into%20the%20coolers%20so%20they%20didn't%3Cem%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3Efreeze.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELoading%20the%20truck%20is%20always%20the%20hard%20part%2C%20as%20it%20requires%20spatial%20skills%20and%20teamwork.%C2%A0We%20didn't%20want%20anything%20shifting%20during%20a%20300-mile%20drive%20home%20but%20wanted%20snacks%20and%20dog%20food%2C%20emergency%20supplies%2C%20and%20extra%20clothing%20accessible%20just%20in%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20bed%20of%20a%20truck%20loaded%20with%20coolers%20and%20plastic%20boxes%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F642f1420c328830019d9f860%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222268%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELoading%20the%20truck%20feels%20like%20a%20game%20of%20Tetris.%3Cp%3EHilary%20Messer-Barrow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20hoisted%20the%20bins%20and%20coolers%20into%20the%20bed%20of%20the%20truck%20and%20my%20husband%20ducked%20under%20the%20canopy%20to%20perfectly%20arrange%20everything.%20Once%20the%20truck%20was%20packed%2C%20we%20took%20our%20dog%20on%20one%20last%20short%20walk%2C%20filled%20our%20tank%20with%20gas%2C%20and%20hit%20the%20road.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20further%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-tips-in-case-of-an-emergency-2019-5%5C%22%3Eprepare%20for%20possible%20emergencies%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20always%20let%20a%20friend%20know%20when%20we're%20leaving%20Whitehorse%20and%20at%20what%20time%20we%20expect%20to%20be%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EOur%20day%20ended%20with%20another%20long%20drive%20%E2%80%94%20and%20lots%20of%20unpacking%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221024%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Snow%20covered%20prairie%20with%20sun%20setting%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F642f146c0c909100186bff1d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22768%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EI%20saw%20some%20amazing%20views%20on%20the%20drive%20back.%3Cp%3EHilary%20Messer-Barrow%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20light%20disappears%2C%20it's%20not%20always%20easy%20to%20see%20where%20the%20road%20ends%20and%20the%20frozen%20ground%20begins%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffood-prices-high-northern-canada-2017-9%5C%22%3Enorthern%20Canada%3C%2Fa%3E.%20With%20that%20in%20mind%2C%20we%20both%20try%20to%20stay%20constantly%20alert%20during%20every%20300-mile%20drive%20home.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFortunately%2C%20the%20best%20part%20of%20the%20drive%20is%20enjoying%20the%20stunning%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flandscapes-you-wont-believe-are-real-2020-7%5C%22%3Eviews%20of%20untouched%20nature%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0until%20the%20sun%20sets.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20we%20got%20home%2C%20we%20were%20exhausted%20from%20our%20long%2C%20incredible%20drive%20%E2%80%94